items.name: Hyocorou - Artist Style (LoRA/Lycoris)
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.😊

These models were trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

About the artist:

Hyocorou has a really interesting and unique artstyle that is hard to get right. Check them out here: ひょころー (@hyocorou) / Twitter

or check out 467231. As they create hentai art you can expect nsfw outputs.

Weights & Prompts

v2.0 (LoCon):

Use a weight of 0.8-1.4. I stayed in the range 0.9-1.0. That includes most character LoRA. Be aware that even the most well-trained charater LoRA can conflict with the style.

LoCon:

Use a weight of 1.0 or lower. When used with character LoRA with their own artstyle (or my Amunero LoRA) you should go a lot lower.

LoRA:

This model was trained on AOM3 and is worse than the new LoCon version in my opinion!

A weight of 1 works when used by itself. For most character lora I used 0.75 but it's all about experimentation. Sometimes a small change in the number of sampling steps or just going up to 0.8 can have massive influence on the output.

Note that this model struggles more with hands than you might be used to and you will regularly need to go over the image in inpaint or edit it manually. I can only guess that this is because of the massive difference between male and female characters drawn by hyocorou.

While hyocorou mostly makes nsfw content in my opinion the soft look works surprisingly well for landscapes.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. I'd also be interested in how the model behaves with other base checkpoints, so why don't you give it a try and throw some images down below! 👇

items.name: TigerstripeAI
items.description:
This is my very first LoRA attempt. I got up the nerve and tried my hand at making one thanks to the wonderful Konyconi-LoRA tutorial. If you haven't already seen their LoRAs, you owe it to yourself to check them out, they're fantastic and I always look forward to their next release. I also used the excellent guide and training Colab from holostrawberry.

About : My LoRA "Tigerstripe" will do just that, add tiger stripes to various objects in the image reasonably well. It excels with cars and trains and buildings but even then I find I might have to add the word "painted" or "colored" sucn as "TigerstripeAI painted dirigible" to get it to work well. can be a bit cantankerous when it comes to certain objects such as rifles or toilets or just about any object where SD expects to see a human holding it or on it. It will put one there (most often a human with tiger stripes and a tiger's head) most of the time unless you use the negative prompt to block it out. Sometimes a tiger tail might appear. I am not sure if this is SD or my failure somewhere in the settings during training - there were no images in the training set with tiger heads or tails, but I only have a thin grasp on what I am doing so it's likely me. If anyone has any ideas on what I did wrong, let me know. Trained using 100 images for 4 repeats, 20 epochs, and 2 batches.

It works best in most cases with a strength between 0.6 and 0.9

How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: Tangbohu Detail Maker LoRA (唐伯虎细节制造LoRA)
items.description:
A Lora mainly used for adding details.

New version 2.5 description

Positive weights can still increase the details of the image, making it particularly suitable for creating things out of thin air. Negative weights can reduce details. Currently, an interesting phenomenon has emerged that some models with 2D or 2.5d effects are gradually restored to 3D realistic effects after using negative weights. Perhaps this interesting effect can be applied to certain projects with special needs, so this version has been uploaded.

Old version description:

The weight range is from - 6 to 3, and both the real style model and the anime animation style model are competent.

Specifically controlled through Lora's weight.

There are two versions, the standard version has a strong emphasis on detail reduction, which leads to the development of the screen towards a different style. Because the content in the prompt has been reduced, the screen has changed. Therefore, -6 does not mean that the quality of the screen has decreased, but may have obtained a relatively pure screen style.

In addition, there is also a Lite version available, which has a relatively small impact and overall controllable changes, making it convenient for fine-tuning numerical values.

Additionally, different screen contents and models have varying levels of support for Lora. A small amount of themes and content will explode after a weight greater than 3.

This Lora model is experimental in nature, and testing support is welcome. Thank you all!

一款主要用于增加细节的lora。

新版2.5说明

正数的权重依然能增加画面细节，特别适合无中生有，负数的权重会减少细节，目前出现了一种有趣的现象，一些2d或者2.5d效果的模型在使用负数权重后模型被逐渐还原成3d真实效果。也许这种有趣的效果能够使用在某些特殊需求的项目上，故此上传了该版本。

旧版说明：

权重范围从-6到3都能起效，不管是真实风格模型还是二次元动漫风格模型都能胜任。

具体通过lora的权重来控制。

有两个版本，标准版力度较强，削减细节方面使得画面朝另外一个画面风格发展，因为将prompt中的内容削减后使得画面产生了变化，所以-6并不意味着画面质量下降，而是可能获得了比较纯粹的画面风格。

另外还准备有lite版本，lite版本的影响较小，整体变化可控，方便数值上进行微调。

另外不同的画面内容和模型对lora的支持程度不同。少量题材和内容将会在大于3的权重后爆炸。

此lora模型为实验性质，欢迎进行测试支持。谢谢大家！

主にディテールを増やすためのlora。

新版2.5の説明

正数の重みは依然として画面の詳細を増やすことができ、特に無中生有に適しており、負の重みは詳細を減らすことができ、現在は興味深い現象が現れており、2 dまたは2.5 d効果のモデルの中には負の重みを使用した後、モデルは徐々に3 d真実効果に還元されている。この興味深い効果は、特定のニーズに特化したアイテムに使用できる可能性があるので、このバージョンをアップロードしました。

旧バージョンの説明：

重みの範囲は-6から3まで有効で、リアルスタイルモデルでも二次元アニメスタイルモデルでも適任です。

具体的にはloraの重みによって制御される。

2つのバージョンがあり、標準版は力が強く、細部を削減することで画面が別の画面スタイルに発展し、proptの内容を削減して画面が変化したため、-6は画面の品質が低下したことを意味するのではなく、比較的純粋な画面スタイルを獲得した可能性がある。

また、liteバージョンも用意されており、liteバージョンの影響は小さく、全体の変化は制御可能で、数値的な微調整が容易である。

また、画面内容やモデルによってloraへのサポート度合いが異なります。少量の題材と内容は3より大きい重みで爆発する。

このloraモデルは実験的な性質であり、テストサポートを歓迎します。ありがとうございました！

디테일을 더하는 데 주로 사용되는 로라.

새 버전 2.5 설명

양수의 가중치는 여전히 화면의 디테일을 증가시킬수 있다. 특히 터무니없이 적합하다. 음수의 가중치는 디테일을 감소시킨다. 현재 재미있는 현상이 나타났다. 일부 2d 또는 2.5d 효과의 모델은 음수의 가중치를 사용한후 모델은 점차 3d의 진실한 효과로 환원되였다.아마도 이런 재미있는 효과는 일부 특수한 수요의 항목에 사용될수 있기에 이 버전을 업로드하였다.

이전 릴리즈 노트:

가중치 범위는 -6에서 3까지 모두 효과가 있으며, 실제 스타일 모델이든 2차 애니메이션 스타일 모델이든 모두 감당할 수 있다.

구체적으로 로라의 권중을 통해 통제한다.

두 가지 버전이 있는데 표준판의 강도가 비교적 강하고 디테일을 줄이는 데 있어 화면이 다른 화면 스타일로 발전했다. 왜냐하면 prompt의 내용을 줄인 후에 화면에 변화가 생겼기 때문에 -6은 화면의 질이 떨어지는 것을 의미하는 것이 아니라 비교적 순수한 화면 스타일을 얻을 수 있다.

또한 lite 버전이 준비되어 있으며 lite 버전의 영향이 적고 전체적인 변화를 제어할 수 있어 수치상 미세조정이 용이하다.

또 화면 내용과 모델에 따라 로라에 대한 지원 정도가 다르다.소량의 소재와 내용은 3보다 큰 가중치 후에 폭발할 것이다.

이 로라 모델은 실험적인 성질이므로 테스트 지원을 환영합니다.감사합니다!

items.name: Woodplanks Peeling Paint Texture
items.description:
Choose SDXL (LoRA) or SD 1.5 version from the menu on the top. Rate, like, and review to help people find the model on the site.

Weathered wood planks Lora, with cracking and peeling paint, from an in-house dataset of textures, photographed on a field trip. The Lora is intended to use as a texture creation helper, for tileable textures, but also works in scenes to texture objects. It adds randomness and structure to various photos. SDXL 1024x1024, SD1.5 768x768. Try to use weights 0.15-0.7 for textures of objects in the scene (higher weights are focusing on texture detail).

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate feature but with more flexiblity

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • Lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • Higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris i found out recently that this method actually lower success rate, so only use when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res step at 20, or 1/2 of sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good result without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results to me.

--

Combining with Attribute LoRa / LyCoris

You may need to do your own testing, but using character weight 0.2 below attribute lora weight yields superior results, if for some reason one features persists not showing or overbake, you may want to lower the weight of the overbaked feature Lora, and then use emphasis () to boost the specific attribute you want.

DDetailer Script

If subject face is small / far away use: DDetailer Script with bbox anime face with default settings except denoiser at 0.2-0.3. You can combine this LoRa with a lot of other Style / Attire / Pose / Acts LoRa, Also works well with character LyCoris.

How to install this script? I kinda forget how because its a bit complicated beacuse you need to install stuff from venv. but a quick google search will land you somewhere in tutorial page.

Please leave a review if you have any critiques or if you find this LoRa good.

items.name: Alejandro Jodorowsky Style
items.description:
Alejandro Jodorowsky is a Chilean-French filmmaker, writer, and artist known for his bold and visionary approach to storytelling, often exploring themes of spirituality, mysticism, and the human condition.

Jodorowsky's work spans across various artistic disciplines, including filmmaking, theater, comic books, and writing. He is renowned for his surreal and unconventional narratives, blending elements of fantasy, symbolism, and mythology.

One of Jodorowsky's most notable films is "El Topo" (1970), a cult classic that challenged cinematic conventions with its psychedelic imagery, religious symbolism, and exploration of existential themes. His later films, such as "The Holy Mountain" (1973) and "Santa Sangre" (1989), continued to push boundaries and captivate audiences with their visually stunning and emotionally charged storytelling.

Apart from filmmaking, Jodorowsky has made significant contributions to the world of comic books. His graphic novel series "The Incal," created in collaboration with artist Moebius, is hailed as a groundbreaking work that blends science fiction, spirituality, and philosophical concepts.

Jodorowsky's artistic pursuits also extend to writing and tarot. He has authored numerous books on topics such as spirituality, psychomagic (a form of therapeutic art), and his own life experiences. He has also designed his own tarot deck, known as the "Jodorowsky Tarot," which combines elements of the traditional tarot with his unique insights and symbolism.

Throughout his career, Jodorowsky has been known for his unconventional and deeply introspective approach to art. His work challenges societal norms, explores the boundaries of human consciousness, and invites viewers and readers to embark on profound journeys of self-discovery and spiritual awakening.

Alejandro Jodorowsky's artistry and visionary storytelling have left a significant impact on the world of cinema, comic books, and beyond. His ability to combine surrealism, mythology, and introspection continues to inspire and captivate audiences, making him a revered and influential figure in the realm of art and imagination.
